source: crates/oxc_formatter_yaml/tests/fixtures/mod.rs
---
==================== Input ====================
# DIVERGENCE: a flow collection either fits on one line or breaks normally;
# a comment inside one breaks it (never Prettier's flat-with-newline form),
# and it stays at its syntactic position.
{"key" # trailing the key
:value}
---
{["key"] # trailing a collection key (one pair, not two entries)
:value}
---
{
# own-line leading
"key": value}
---
[a: b # trailing the value
, c]
---
key: [ # kept inside the brackets
  a,
  b ]
---
[last, # comments before the closing bracket
# become own-line end comments
]

